      • Allowed_usage_start_page

        public static final UnitOfUsages Allowed_usage_start_page
        Page number where allowed usage begins. should contain an absolute page number, counting the cover as page 1. (This type of page numbering should not be used where the e-publication has no fixed pagination). Use with (max number of) Pages, Percentage of content, or End page to specify pages allowed in Preview.

        NOTE: Introduced in Onix3

      • Allowed_usage_end_page

        public static final UnitOfUsages Allowed_usage_end_page
        Page number at which allowed usage ends. should contain an absolute page number, counting the cover as page 1. (This type of page numbering should not be used where the e-publication has no fixed pagination). Use with Start page to specify pages allowed in a preview.

        NOTE: Introduced in Onix3

      • Allowed_usage_start_page_

        public static final UnitOfUsages Allowed_usage_start_page_
        Page number where allowed usage begins. should contain an absolute page number, counting the cover as page 1. (This type of page numbering should not be used where the e-publication has no fixed pagination). Use with (max number of) Pages, Percentage of content, or End page to specify pages allowed in Preview.

        NOTE: Deprecated in Onix3
